article.headline: VMI 90, James Madison 83
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams scored 30 points to push VMI ahead of James Madison 90-83, the Keydets' first win over the Dukes since 1988 Wednesday night. VMI (2-2) edged out James Madison (2-1) early and maintained the lead through much of the first half, letting the Dukes no closer than two points until a jumper from Ben Louis finally pushed the Dukes ahead 36-35, with 3:34 on the clock. The teams traded baskets and went into the half 42-42. A three-pointer by Chavis Holmes pushed VMI ahead early in the second half, but James Madison's Terrance Carter added 17 of his game total 23 points to help tie the score 81-81 with less 2:27 to go. Williams answered with a seven-point run, and the Dukes never recovered. VMI's Travis Holmes scored 18, and Christian Hunter had 11. James Madison's Heiden Ratner had 15 and Pierre Curtis scored 10. The win snapped an eight-game losing streak against the Dukes.
